creator.organizationName: The Barbados Museum and Historical Society

abstract.para: This data set records the collection of shells donated to the Barbados Museum and Historical Society by Dr. Basil Weatherhead.

geographicCoverage.geographicDescription: The Barbados Museum and Historical Society is located within the Barbados UNESCO World Heritage Site of Bridgetown and it's Garrison. Formerly a military prison for the British, it was converted into a museum in 1933.

taxonomicCoverage.generalTaxonomicCoverage: All specimens were identified to family or species using various resources to identify the taxonomic data

description.para: Each specimen has an ownership record, is classified, photographed and entered into the database
The extent of this study is confined to the collections which have already been donated to the Barbados Museum and historical Society

samplingDescription.para: For the BMHS there is no field sampling; specimens are donated to the museum

project.title: Improving Biodiversity data accessibility in the Caribbean countries of Trinidad & Tobago, Barbados and Suriname

abstract.para: This project was conducted to prepare the biodiversity information held at national institutes for online publication

funding.para: Funding for this project was attained through a grant from GBIF
